HEADWORD: Dubiosity
<hw>Du`bi*os"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Dubiosities</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.
<ets>dubiosus</ets>.]</ety> <def>The state of being doubtful; a doubtful
statement or thing.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Men often swallow falsities for truths, <qex>dubiosities</qex> for
certainties, possibilities for feasibilities.</q> <rj><qau>Sir T.
Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dubious</ent>⟦br⟧
